{"word":"εὔεδρος","slug":"εὔεδρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὔεδρος</b></el> <el>(εὔ-εδρος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕδρα'><el>ἕδρα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>with beautiful seat, on stately throne</i>, of gods, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of a ship, = <el>ἐΰσσελμος</el>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>easy to sit</i>, <el>ἵππος</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}